## SQL Schema

```sql
CREATE TABLE Users (
    user_id INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
    name VARCHAR(100),
    email VARCHAR(100),
    password VARCHAR(100),
    role VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE Books (
    book_id INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
    book_name VARCHAR(200),
    genre VARCHAR(50),
    category VARCHAR(50),
    author_type VARCHAR(20),
    language VARCHAR(20),
    rating VARCHAR(20),
    availability VARCHAR(20)
);

CREATE TABLE Issue_Records (
    record_id INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
    user_no VARCHAR(20),
    book_id INT,
    book_name VARCHAR(200),
    due_date DATE,
    FOREIGN KEY (book_id) REFERENCES Books(book_id)
);
```

## Database Description

The database consists of three tables: Users, Books, and Issue_Records. The Books table stores the dataset used for recommendations, while Issue_Records stores issued book information. Users and library staff access the system through the Users table.
